Defendant Jennifer M Sharp in court with attorney Joseph Smith.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count 1.  Court finds her guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.    State gives recommendations.  Attorney Smith makes statements.  Jennifer Sharp makes statements.  Victim makes statements. The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   
Count 1

60 days jail, no HUBER, STAYED

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Continue with mental health treatment. 
*No violent contact with:  Victim listed in the criminal complaint. 
COURT COSTS:  $343.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
